---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import {getBrandCharts} from "../lib/content/brand-charts";
const charts=getBrandCharts();
---
<BaseLayout title="Goalie leg-pad size charts | Goalie Gear Fit" description="Reviewed Bauer, CCM, TRUE, Warrior and Brian's goalie leg-pad size charts with honest measurement and fit guidance.">
 <section class="home-hero content"><p class="eyebrow">Independent sizing reference</p><h1>Goalie leg-pad size charts you can trace to reviewed data</h1><p class="lede">Compare manufacturer sizing rules without nearest-size guesses. Choose a brand, use the exact measurement method it publishes, and verify the final fit at the knee block.</p><p class="hero-actions"><a class="button" href="/calculator">Find my size</a><a href="/charts/">Browse size charts</a><a href="/guides/how-to-measure-goalie-pads">Learn how to measure</a></p></section>
 <section class="card" aria-labelledby="brand-heading"><div class="content"><p class="eyebrow">Five reviewed brands</p><h2 id="brand-heading">Choose your goalie pad brand</h2><p>Each chart explains the brand's own measurement method, boundaries, gaps and fit cautions.</p></div><div class="brand-grid">{charts.map(chart=><article class="brand-card"><h3><a href={`/charts/${chart.slug}`}>{chart.brand} size chart</a></h3><p>{chart.rules.length} reviewed sizing rules · {chart.categories.length} chart section{chart.categories.length===1?"":"s"}</p></article>)}</div></section>
 <section class="home-steps" aria-labelledby="steps-heading"><div class="content"><p class="eyebrow">Before choosing a size</p><h2 id="steps-heading">Measure, compare, then verify</h2></div><ol class="step-grid"><li><strong>Use the named method.</strong><span>Floor-to-knee and ankle-to-knee are not interchangeable.</span></li><li><strong>Respect boundaries and gaps.</strong><span>An overlap can yield adjacent options; missing evidence stays cannot determine.</span></li><li><strong>Check the pad physically.</strong><span>Confirm knee-block landing with your skates and protection on.</span></li></ol></section>
 <section class="card content"><h2>How this reference earns trust</h2><p>The site consumes a schema-validated published dataset, tests boundary and unsupported cases in CI, and keeps source dates visible. It does not publish raw chart snapshots or infer a missing manufacturer size.</p><p><a href="/methodology">Read the methodology and provenance</a> · <a href="/guides/thigh-rise-and-fit-check">Review thigh rise and fit checks</a></p></section>
</BaseLayout>
